One of the raps on Texas in the early days, and again, was that one of the raps, the criticisms, was that they bought, quote, indiscriminately, that the tower was filled with things they didn't even know was in there.
Is that a Justify or a Justify?
Well, for a time we had, we were buying things and they were stored almost everywhere.
And then we got a big building out there.
And then finally got this new building.
Most of the actual manuscript material and the extremely valuable books were kept in the main building.
Tower?
Yeah.
No, the old Rare Books Library used to be
It's located where the president's office is now, which is on the fourth floor of the main building.
That's the tower building.
But the fourth floor is on the front, looking down toward the capitol.
That's where it was.
That whole top floor there was the dump of all the rebels.
And it was run by a lady that entered Fanny Radford for years, who, I suppose, didn't remember Thomas A. Wise.
He's part of my book.
Good.

that ultimately came here.
